</p>

<p>
  For the last two weeks at Ada, we were working on creating our personal blogs
  (which you are so kindly reading now!). When I was creating this site, it was
  very easy to dive into structuring the HTML, formatting the CSS and tweaking
  the JavaScript (make sure to check out my konami easter egg on the dessert page!)
  haphazardly without any long term plan for what I wanted to accomplish.
  When I started writing out and organizing lists of what I wanted to accomplish
  on Trello my workflow improved dramatically because I could move from task to
  task quickly without staring at my screen slackjawed wondering what to do next.
</p>
